# Copy this file to `.env.local` (same directory) to point the dev shell at a
# kernel of your choosing. `.env.local` is gitignored (the `*.local` rule) — it's
# a per-machine override, never committed, so your local setup can't leak into a
# clone or a production build.
#
# VITE_KERNEL_URL — which kernel the shell talks to.
#   Leave it UNSET (no `.env.local` at all) and the shell defaults to the
#   production kernel, https://kernel.os-joy.com — fine for looking around.
#   But you can only `/login` against a kernel where your address is a
#   registered symbiot, so to sign in against a kernel you're running locally,
#   set it to that kernel's address (its default dev port is 9713):
VITE_KERNEL_URL=http://127.0.0.1:9713
#
# Vite reads env vars only at startup — if `yarn dev` is already running,
# restart it after creating `.env.local`; a hot reload won't pick this up.
# Open the shell at localhost:5173 or 127.0.0.1:5173 (both are in the kernel's
# CORS allow-list); any other host or port the browser will block.
